ses who wished to establish a repository for significant documents relating to nursing history in the Midwest.  Centers for Culture and Social Change  Our Centers for Cultural Understanding and Social Change are dedicated to fostering greater acceptance and understanding, ensuring that students make the most of their experiences at UIC while also serving as a "second home" for students and a resource for educational materials, music, and art. Visit the cultral centers’ websites for contact information and hours of operation.                       Live view from the top of University Hall View Now           Related Resources    Visit Campus  Explore UIC  Contact Admissions                    UnderGraduate      Graduate & Professional                 Office of Admissions  Main Office  1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-4350 Contact UIC Admissions    Visitors Center  1220 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 413-1726                 Mailing Address  Undergraduate  Office of Undergraduate Admissions (MC 018) University of Illinois at Chicago 1200 West Harrison Street, Suite 1100 Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Contact Undergraduate Admissions     Graduate & Professional  The graduate and professional application process is paperless. Please do not mail materials unless expressly requested. Contact Graduate and Professional Admissions                             Privacy Statement  Nondiscrimination Statement  Site Map  Accessibility  Site Home  UIC Home  Login  Webmaster  Copyright © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois Facebook  Twitter  YouTube  Accessibility         T     CookieSettings     